Visualization

1) The Mrs.President pie charts would be better as bar charts One problem is that the yes/no sum dont total 100%, so in that case, I would just present the yes response. It should also be 2 separate graphics, age is a different variable from gender.

president <- tribble(
  ~age,     ~yes, ~no, 
  "1under45",  79, 16,
  "2b45-64",    69, 22,
  "365over",   44, 39
)

president
## # A tibble: 3 x 3
##   age        yes    no
##   <chr>    <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 1under45  79.0  16.0
## 2 2b45-64   69.0  22.0
## 3 365over   44.0  39.0
ggplot(data=president)+
  geom_bar(mapping=aes(x=age, y=yes), stat = "identity")

ggplot(data=president, aes(x=age, y=yes))+ geom_bar()

counts <- table(mtcars\(vs, mtcars\)gear) barplot(counts, main=Car Distribution by Gears and VS, xlab=Number of Gears, col=c(darkblue,red), legend = rownames(counts), beside=TRUE)

2) Reproduce diamonds graphics

3) Make one change on the code and make graphics more useful.

library(tidyverse)

ggplot(data = diamonds, mapping = aes(x = cut, y = carat, fill=color))+
  geom_boxplot(position='identity')+ 
  coord_flip() +
  xlab("CUT OF DIAMOND")+
  ylab("CARAT OF DIAMOND") 

ggplot(data = diamonds, mapping = aes(x = cut, y = price, fill=color))+
  geom_boxplot(position='identity')+ 
  coord_flip() +
  xlab("CUT OF DIAMOND")+
  ylab("PRICE OF DIAMOND") 

ggplot(data = diamonds, mapping = aes(x = reorder(cut, carat, FUN=median), y = price, fill=color))+
  geom_boxplot(position='identity')+ 
  coord_flip() +
  xlab("CUT OF DIAMOND")+
  ylab("CARAT OF DIAMOND")

3) Number of diamonds price > 1000 and carat < 1.5

library(nycflights13)

flights_sml <- select(flights, 
  year:day, 
  ends_with("delay"), 
  distance, 
  air_time
)
mutate(flights_sml,
  gain = arr_delay - dep_delay,
  speed = distance / air_time * 60
)
